The phrase ne moleslus sis occurs five times in the Mostellaria (cf. 601, 771, 877, 886), and is a general equivalent for the English ‘ shut up ’. This form of the prohibition (ne with the present suly'mzctive) is common in old Latin, e. g. 468, though in many passages it is doubtful whether we have a prohibition or a final clause; see on 215.
